  "texts": [
    "The two most prominent neural operators are DeepONets 13 [139] and Fourier neural operators [140].",
    "DeepONetIn DeepONets [139], illustrated in Fig. 4, the task of predicting the operator û(λ; x) is split up into two sub-tasks:• the prediction of N P basis functions t(x) (TrunkNet),• the prediction of the correspondingN P problem-specific coefficients b(λ) (BranchNet).The basis is predicted by the TrunkNet with parameters θ T via an evaluation at coordinates x.",
    "The coefficients are estimated from the coefficients λ using the BranchNet parametrized by θ B and, thus, specific to the problem being solved.",
    "Taking the dot product over the evaluated basis and the coefficients yields the solution prediction û(λ; x).t(x) = F T F N N (x; θ T) (10) b(λ) = F B F N N (λ; θ B) (11) û(x) = b(λ) • t(x)(12)Applications can be found in [141][142][143][144][145][146][147][148][149][150][151][152][153].",
    "DeepONets have also been extended with physics-informed loss functions [154][155][156]."
  ],
